# Shim UEFI Bootloader Stub
# This is a placeholder for shim.efi (signed UEFI bootloader)
# 
# In production:
# 1. Download signed shim from your Linux distribution:
#    - Ubuntu: apt download shim-signed
#    - RHEL: dnf download shim-x64
#    - Debian: apt download shim-efi-amd64-signed
# 
# 2. Extract and install:
#    unzip shim-signed_*.deb
#    cp ./usr/lib/shim/shimx64.efi to this location
#
# Boot Mode: UEFI (Standard)
# Partition Table: GPT
# File System: FAT32 (EFI System Partition)
# Compatibility: Modern systems (Windows 8+, Linux, macOS Intel)
#
# UEFI Boot Flow:
# 1. Device performs UEFI PXE boot
# 2. DHCP server provides bootfile: /efi/shimx64.efi
# 3. Device fetches shimx64.efi via TFTP/HTTP
# 4. Shim verifies grubx64.efi signature
# 5. GRUB chainloads the OS image
# 6. Image deployment begins
#
# Signing: This shim is pre-signed by the Linux distribution
# Secure Boot: Works with Secure Boot DISABLED
